				<br class="hide" />
<!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="maincontent" --><!-- InstanceEndEditable -->
<!-- <#MAINCONTENT> -->
<!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="MainContent" -->
  <p style="margin-top: 0;">Students in the Faculty of Arts and Science who wish to participate on a student exchange may obtain information on the various exchanges offered by contacting Roberto  Chen-Rangel, Academic Counsellor, Faculty of Arts &amp; Sciences at (514) 848-2424 ext. 5378 or by  e-mail at&nbsp;<a href="mailto:rchenrangel@artsci.concordia.ca">rchenrangel@artsci.concordia.ca </a>or by contacting <a href="../arts/index.html">Concordia International</a> at (514) 848-2424 ext.4987.</p>
  <h2>Eligibility</h2>
  <p>In order to be eligible, students in the Faculty of Arts and Science must have a last annual GPA of 3.00 or above and also to have been a full-time student in the academic year preceding the exchange and their application.</p>
  <h2>Procedures</h2>
  <p>To receive permission to go on a student exchange, students must complete a <a href="http://artsandscience.concordia.ca/currentstudents/degreerequirementsandprocedures/studentrequestforms/">Student Request Form</a> and the application package available through <a href="../arts/index.html">Concordia International</a>.</p>
  <h2>Bursaries</h2>
  <p>Bursaries for students participating on Student Exchange are available for Quebec residents who are completing a University degree. Amounts range from $750 to $1000, depending upon destination. For more information, please visit <a href="../arts/index.html">Concordia International</a>.</p>
<h2>Study Abroad Program</h2>
<p>Students interested in studying at an institution that  does not have an exchange agreement with Concordia may still be granted  permission to do so. In this situation, students would be required to pay  tuition directly to their host university. In order to be considered for this  option, students must submit a <a href="../arts/currentstudents/studyabroad/documents/Student_Request_Form_2009-10.pdf">Student  Request Form</a> to the Student Academic Services office.</p>
